I've seen a lot of different replies on here & reasons, I think it really depends on the farm! at our farm we leave the calves with the moms for a few hours but there is typically 5-10 cows in the calving pen at a time so it's safer for the calf to get moved into its own pen to prevent getting stepped on & from picking up any diseases from the bedding since it's a lot easier to keep fresh clean bedding in a smaller calf pen. the calf always gets the moms colostrum and lots of love and attention from us. sometimes Holsteins & dairy cows aren't overly interested in taking care of their babies either so it allows us to keep a closer eye on the calf and make sure it is getting enough milk. hope that gives some insight!
